      title: 'PCOS and Skin',
      humorLevel: 'medium',
      content: `PCOS affects 1 in 10 women and your skin often shows it first.

**PCOS Skin Signs:**
- Persistent acne (especially jaw/chin)
- Excess facial hair (hirsutism)
- Scalp hair thinning
- Dark patches (acanthosis nigricans)
- Skin tags

**Why PCOS Causes These:**
- Elevated androgens
- Insulin resistance
- Chronic low-grade inflammation
- Elevated cortisol

**The Double Bind:**
PCOS makes you gain weight. Weight gain worsens PCOS. Insulin resistance drives both. Breaking the cycle requires addressing the root.

**PCOS Treatment Approaches:**

| Approach | How It Helps |
|----------|--------------|
| Insulin sensitizers (Metformin) | Reduces insulin, lowers androgens |
| Anti-androgen birth control | Blocks androgen effects |
| Spironolactone | Blocks androgens directly |
| Inositol supplements | Improves insulin sensitivity |
| Low-carb/low GI diet | Reduces insulin spikes |
| Exercise | Improves insulin sensitivity |

**Getting Diagnosed:**
- Irregular periods (or none)
- Elevated androgens (blood test or symptoms)
- Polycystic ovaries on ultrasound
(Need 2 of 3 for diagnosis)`,
