      id: 'cycle-syncing',
      title: 'Skincare Across Your Cycle',
      humorLevel: 'medium',
      content: `Your skin changes throughout your menstrual cycle:

**Days 1-5 (Menstruation)**
- Hormones at lowest point
- Skin may be dry and sensitive
- Focus: Gentle, hydrating products
- Skip strong actives if skin is irritated

**Days 6-13 (Follicular Phase)**
- Estrogen rising
- Skin at its best
- Focus: Can be more aggressive with actives
- Good time for: Retinoids, exfoliation

**Days 14-16 (Ovulation)**
- Estrogen peaks, some testosterone spike
- Skin often glowing
- Focus: Maintain routine
- May notice slight oiliness starting

**Days 17-28 (Luteal Phase)**
- Progesterone rises, then drops
- Sebum production increases
- PMS breakouts start
- Focus: Oil control, don't pick
- Increase: Niacinamide, BHA

**Preventive Approach:**
Know when your breakouts come. Start ramping up sebum-control products a few days before. Some dermatologists prescribe cyclic doxycycline or spironolactone for severe cyclic acne.`,
